   "source": [
    "# Case study 3: Pancreatic endocrinogenesis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c722ce38-4fdf-402e-bc8a-67dd276441db",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This tutorial shows how cellDancer derives cell fates in the embedding space. \n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial also displays cellDancer's ability to decipher cell identity based on the cell-specific reaction rates.\n",
    "\n",
    "Below is the case study for pancreatic endocrinogenesis. We follow the gene and cell filtering methods of [Bergen et.al](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41587-020-0591-3). 3,696 cells with 2,000 genes are selected. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "418956f5-4eac-425b-97a7-123e6dabe701",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Import packages"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a890bb05-40a4-406d-87db-182ea6ac3b2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To run the notebook locally, [Installation](installation.html) could be referred to install the environment and dependencies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "1ceb600e-9598-4fd1-85fb-9bd43b97ee4d",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# import packages\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import math\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import celldancer as cd\n",
    "import celldancer.cdplt as cdplt\n",
    "from celldancer.cdplt import colormap"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5a99e119-7072-437d-8d93-1dcfb81c8e79",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load cellDancer result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5adce882-b0ac-4e05-96ff-5729eae7a3e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use the preprocessed data [PancreaticEndocrinogenesis_cell_type_u_s.csv.zip](https://drive.google.com/file/d/16hV9t66edOgjCmoBuEfekS3ijtL1fYNc/view?usp=sharing) to predict the RNA velocities (see the details of pre-processing steps [Data Preparation](data_preprocessing.html)). \n",
    "Below are the command we used for the RNA velocity estimation. \n",
    "    \n",
    "    cellDancer_df = cd.velocity(cell_type_u_s, permutation_ratio=0.5, n_jobs=8)\n",
    "The prediction result can be downloaded from [PancreaticEndocrinogenesis_cellDancer_estimation.csv.zip](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1n_ZxAXuKB1BzcpIDkPj3XdOs-Ni45yD7/view?usp=sharing). "

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "34cdc007-f5f1-4073-b537-e3095ad2f558",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Project the RNA velocity onto the embedding space"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e3d3dcdf-60fa-4b27-833b-6d3280b05a0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We calculate the projection of RNA velocity on the embedding with ```cd.compute_cell_velocity()```. The projected direction on embedding space, i.e. columns 'velocity1' and 'velocity2' are added to the original dataframe. We use ```cdplt.scatter_cell()``` to display the predicted direction on embedding space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "46bff124-e23f-44ff-b862-139a7903ca62",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Compute cell velocity\n",
    "cellDancer_df=cd.compute_cell_velocity(cellDancer_df=cellDancer_df, projection_neighbor_size=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot cell velocity\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "im = cdplt.scatter_cell(ax, cellDancer_df, colors=colormap.colormap_pancreas, alpha=0.5, s=10, velocity=True, legend='on', min_mass=5, arrow_grid=(20,20))\n",
    "ax.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9238fb72-2489-4b75-906c-c0de01c6930b",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Build UMAP based on reaction rates"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f76ab241-869c-4836-8ab7-ca5a71f26dce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use ```cd.embedding_kinetic_para()``` to build the UMAP based on the predicted alpha, predicted beta, predicted gamma, or all of the three."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "54e87eb7-23e4-42e4-a67e-6f2ab7d71107",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cellDancer_df=cd.embedding_kinetic_para(cellDancer_df,'alpha')\n",
    "cellDancer_df=cd.embedding_kinetic_para(cellDancer_df,'beta')\n",
    "cellDancer_df=cd.embedding_kinetic_para(cellDancer_df,'gamma')\n",
    "cellDancer_df=cd.embedding_kinetic_para(cellDancer_df,'alpha_beta_gamma')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c9c9618f-ea2c-4d17-b8a8-cf8bf68772e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We visualize the UMAP of kinetic parameter(s) with ```cdplt.plot_kinetic_para()```."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "8ca3631b-3e8e-4acc-afb4-069382cd74c7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<AxesSubplot:title={'center':'UMAP of gamma'}>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(ncols=4, figsize=(16,8))\n",
    "cdplt.plot_kinetic_para(ax[0], 'alpha_beta_gamma', cellDancer_df, color_map=colormap.colormap_pancreas)\n",
    "cdplt.plot_kinetic_para(ax[1], 'alpha', cellDancer_df, color_map=colormap.colormap_pancreas)\n",
    "cdplt.plot_kinetic_para(ax[2], 'beta', cellDancer_df, color_map=colormap.colormap_pancreas)\n",
    "cdplt.plot_kinetic_para(ax[3], 'gamma', cellDancer_df, color_map=colormap.colormap_pancreas)"
   ]
  }
